Class ZstandardCompression

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.jetty.util.component.AbstractLifeCycle
org.eclipse.jetty.util.component.ContainerLifeCycle
org.eclipse.jetty.compression.Compression
org.eclipse.jetty.compression.zstandard.ZstandardCompression
All Implemented Interfaces:
Container, Destroyable, Dumpable, Dumpable.DumpableContainer, LifeCycle
public class ZstandardCompression extends Compression
Compression for Zstandard.

Note about ByteBufferPool: the zstd-jni project requires ByteBuffer implementations that are array backed with a zero arrayOffset.

See Also:
  • RFC 8478 - Zstandard Compression and the application/zstd Media Type
  • Uses zstd-jni

  • Method Details

    • acquireByteBuffer

      public RetainableByteBuffer.Mutable acquireByteBuffer(int length)
      Description copied from class: Compression
      Acquire a RetainableByteBuffer that is managed by this Compression implementation which is suitable for compressed output from an EncoderSink or compressed input from a DecoderSource.

      It is recommended to use this method so that any compression specific details can be managed by this Compression implementation (such as ByteOrder or buffer pooling)

      Specified by:
      acquireByteBuffer in class Compression
      Parameters:
      length - the requested size of the buffer
      Returns:
      the ByteBuffer suitable for this compression implementation.
